<Objective>
Evaluate the candidate summary against the source using turn-by-turn questions from runtime.
</Objective>
<Context>
Each question expects a binary yes/no answer.
Answer strictly in runtime order.
</Context>
<Inputs>
Candidate Summary XML:
{{ summary_xml }}

Source Transcript:
{{ source_text }}

Total Questions:
{{ total_questions }}
</Inputs>
<Output contract>
Call tool `submit_answer` once per turn until all questions are answered.
The current question_id is always in the latest `Turn instruction` message.
Never answer a previous or future question_id.
Return no plain text outside tool calls.
Each tool call must include `summary_evidence_quote` copied exactly from candidate summary XML.
Quote relevance mode: `{{ quote_relevance_mode }}`.
Minimum shared tokens (lexical mode): `{{ quote_relevance_min_shared_tokens }}`.
Minimum distinctive shared tokens (lexical mode): `{{ quote_relevance_min_distinctive_shared_tokens }}`.
Semantic threshold (semantic mode): `{{ quote_relevance_semantic_threshold }}`.
Auto repair invalid quotes: `{{ quote_relevance_auto_repair }}`.
Auto repair minimum score: `{{ quote_relevance_repair_min_score }}`.
Auto repair minimum candidate chars: `{{ quote_relevance_min_candidate_chars }}`.
If mode is `off`, relevance overlap checks are disabled, but quote grounding is still required.
</Output contract>
